Name: Inclined Dumbell Press
Description: Set incline to 15degrees, and press with chest.

Name: Dumbell Overhead Press
Description: Set incline to just below vertical, and press with shoulders.

Name: High Cable Flies
Description: Set pulleys at shoulder height or slightly above, and lock out elbows while pressing.

Name: Lateral Raises
Description: Bring out arms laterally, in line with shoulder joint.

Name: Tricep Overhead Extension
Description: Vetically seated, point elbow near-perpendicular to the ground, and extend arm upwards.

Name: Tricep Pushdown
Description: Using a rope or a bar, press down with elbows locked in, to the sides.

Name: Lateral Pulldown
Description: Using minmial arm strength, pull elbows down to waist while engaging lats.

Name: Cable rows
Description: Back upright, pull weight without motion of lower back. Focus on midsection and lat engagement.

Name: Preacher Curls
Description: Using an EZ Bar on a preacher bench, focus on bicep contraction and negatives.

Name: Dumbell Hammer Curl
Description: Elbows nearly locked in, bring weight up to chest with a sideways grip on the dumbells.

Name: Reverse Grip EZ Bar Curls
Description: Using an EZ Bar and elbows tucked in, pull weight up using forearms.

Name: Dumbell Wrist Curls
Description: With weights to the sides, curl the weight soleley with your fingers, for forearm flexion.
